## 8️⃣ Security & Edge Case Review

| Check | Result |
|-------|--------|
| Empty search | ✅ PASS — Returns 400 `"Keyword is required."` |
| Extremely long keyword (5000 chars) | ⚠️ WARN — Server processed it (200 OK). No input length limit |
| SQL-like injection string | ✅ PASS — Treated as regular keyword, no vulnerability |
| Protected route without token | ✅ PASS — 401 returned |
| Network requests for data leaks | ✅ PASS — No passwords, secrets, or sensitive data in responses |
| Email validation | ✅ PASS — Mongoose regex `/^\S+@\S+\.\S+$/` |
| Password min length | ✅ PASS — 6 character minimum enforced server-side |
| `MONGO_URI` exposed | ⚠️ WARN — `MONGO_URI` not in [.env](file:///c:/Users/dasar/DropGravity%20Pro/server/.env) file, likely set at system level |

> [!WARNING]
> No **rate limiting** on any endpoint. An attacker could spam `/api/auth/register` or `/api/products/analyze` without throttling. Consider adding `express-rate-limit` before production.

